        'Consider: attachment theory (does secure attachment expand or limit self-knowledge?), the ethics of care (is dependency a failure or a realistic acknowledgement of our nature?)',
        'The strongest counterargument: love may be the primary context in which we discover who we actually are — what we need, what we fear, how we behave when the stakes are high',
        'End with a claim about what conditions allow love to be a context for genuine self-knowledge rather than a flight from it',
