        'Emotional labour, the precariat, and the gig economy all provide structural mechanisms to analyse',
        'The strongest counterargument: individual agency and work-life boundary-setting are not nothing — some burnout is exacerbated by individual failure to set limits',
        'End with a claim about what structural changes (labour law, working time regulation, collective bargaining, UBI) would actually address the structural causes',
